records.addlTxt:
Called 14CF73 and 15CM300. Defendant Brina J. Karpinski in court, in custody with attorney Jaclyn Shelton.  Yolanda J. Tienstra appeared for the State of Wisconsin in case 15CM300. Attorney Gilbert Thompson appeared for the State of Wisconsin in case 14CF73. All parties have received the document, none offer any corrections to document. Discussion held on presentence credit - 163 days credit 14CF73; and 85 days credit 15CM300 agreed to by all parties. Ct. heard, finds victim rights compliance. Atty Thompson heard on argument. Atty Tienstra heard on argument. Atty Shelton heard. Def. makes statement. Ct. heard, imposes sent:

14CF73
9 mos. DCJ w/ H&T, to comm. forthwith;
To run concurrent w/ 15CM300.


15CM300;
6 mos. DCJ w/ H&T, to comm. forthwith;
To run concurrent w/ 14CF73.

Ct. heard, if Atty Shelton is able to present to the court a viable situation for the Def., the court may consider modifying the sentence.  Present credit is as stated above 163 days in 14CF73 and 85 days in 15CM300. Any unpaid/remaining obligation will be a civil judgment.
